From: ASUS ProArt PX13 debug <snd-repair@local>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] ASoC: sdw_utils: split playback channels across codecs

When a dai_link has N codec DAIs and the PCM stream presents N channels
in playback, assign one channel per codec via ch_maps (ch_maps[i].ch_mask
= BIT(i)).

Capture already splits channels when aggregating multiple codecs; playback
used step = 0 so every codec received the full channel mask. That is
correct for duplicated mono but breaks the common case of one physical
speaker per codec (stereo with two amps, quad with four amps, etc.).

The new branch mirrors the capture-side constraint (ch divisible by
num_codecs) in the symmetric playback case ch == num_codecs. Other
playback layouts (mono to N codecs, stereo to N>2 codecs) keep the
previous behavior.

Reported-on: AMD ACP70 2x TAS2783; ACPI tables also describe Intel MTL
with up to 4x TAS2783 on one link (4ch -> 4 codecs).

Signed-off-by: ASUS ProArt PX13 debug <snd-repair@local>
---
 sound/soc/sdw_utils/soc_sdw_utils.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/sdw_utils/soc_sdw_utils.c b/sound/soc/sdw_utils/soc_sdw_utils.c
--- a/sound/soc/sdw_utils/soc_sdw_utils.c
+++ b/sound/soc/sdw_utils/soc_sdw_utils.c
@@ -1180,6 +1180,13 @@ int asoc_sdw_hw_params(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream,
 
 	/* Identical data will be sent to all codecs in playback */
 	if (substream->stream == SNDRV_PCM_STREAM_PLAYBACK) {
+		num_codecs = rtd->dai_link->num_codecs;
+		if (num_codecs > 1 && ch == num_codecs) {
+			for_each_link_ch_maps(rtd->dai_link, i, ch_maps)
+				ch_maps->ch_mask = BIT(i);
+			return 0;
+		}
+
 		ch_mask = GENMASK(ch - 1, 0);
 		step = 0;
 	} else {
